dentifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/State","preciseIdentifier":"s:22ComposableArchitecture7ReducerP5StateQa","text":"State","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:13CasePathsCore0A8PathableP","text":"CasePathable","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A case path from parent state to a case containing child state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"toCaseState"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A case path from parent action to a case containing child actions.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"toCaseAction"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A reducer that will be invoked with child actions against child state when it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"present"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"case"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The fileID."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"fileID"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The filePath."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"filePath"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The line."}]}],"name":"line"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The column.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"column"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Return Value","anchor":"return-value","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A reducer that combines the child reducer with the parent reducer.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For example, if a parent feature’s state is expressed as an enum of multiple children","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"states, then ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifCaseLet"},{"text":" can run a child reducer on a particular case of the enum:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Reducer","struct Parent {","  enum State {","    case loggedIn(Authenticated.State)","    case loggedOut(Unauthenticated.State)","  }","  enum Action {","    case loggedIn(Authenticated.Action)","    case loggedOut(Unauthenticated.Action)","    \/\/ ...","  }","","  var body: some Reducer<State, Action> {","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifCaseLet(\\.loggedIn, action: \\.loggedIn) {","      Authenticated()","    }","    .ifCaseLet(\\.loggedOut, action: \\.loggedOut) {","      Unauthenticated()","    }","  }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"ifCaseLet","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" operator does a number of things to try to enforce correctness:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It runs the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the parent feature to change the case of the child enum, in which case the child","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"feature would not be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child enum case changes."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is still possible for a parent feature higher up in the application to change the case of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the enum before the child has a chance to react to the action. In such cases a runtime"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"warning is shown in Xcode to let you 